Send a task to {{PEER_NAME}} and wait for their reply.

1. Call `cli_connect__send` with to="{{PEER_NAME}}" and body="$ARGUMENTS". Note the returned `sent_id`.
2. Output ONLY: `📤 Sent to {{PEER_NAME}}: $ARGUMENTS`

3. Wait for reply — loop:
   a. Call `cli_connect__poll`
   b. Got `{"message":{...}}` with type "reply" and originalId matching sent_id:
      - Output ONLY: `📬 {{PEER_NAME}} replied: [body]`
      - (Auto-acknowledged — no acknowledge call needed.)
      - STOP. Return control to the human.
   c. Got `{"message":{...}}` with type "task":
      - Execute it silently → call `cli_connect__reply` → continue loop
   d. Got `{"inbox":"timeout"}` → loop again immediately (no output)
